exploration

Class ExplorationParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • exploration.ExplorationParameters
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommCostParams, LatBuffParams, LatencyParams, LatProcBuffParams, LatProcParams, MaxwrkloadCommClusterParams, PeriodParams, PeriodProcParams, PeriodProcUnfolding, PeriodUnfoldingParams, WrkldImbalCommClusterParams, WrkLoadCommCostParams

    public abstract class ExplorationParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    An interface class to the design space exploration algorithms. This class contains methods which any design space algorithm needs to perform an exploration of a given design space.
    Author:
    Pranav Tendulkar

      • setConstraint

        public abstract void setConstraint(int dimension,
                 int value)
        Set a constraint for a particular dimension. This will be called for every query when exploration algorithm wants to set a cost constraint for evaluation.
        Parameters:
        dimension - dimension of which the constraint will be set
        value - value to which the constraint will be set

      • getCostsFromModel

        public abstract int[] getCostsFromModel()
        If the query was SAT, then this method will be called to get the costs from the model given by the solver.
        Returns:
        integer costs for every dimension taken from the model
